2026-07-19 09:05:00 PDT — Issue #5 validation started

Root-cause analysis (5 whys)
1. Users could not explore immediately because a launch modal blocked the scene.
2. The modal existed to initiate pointer lock.
3. Pointer lock was used for game-style mouse-look.
4. Unbounded mouse deltas could rotate the camera far away from the landmark.
5. The interaction was designed around a flight-game convention instead of the core job: inspect the Golden Gate Bridge with minimal friction.

Root-cause correction
- Removed the launch and resume gates.
- Removed pointer-lock and pointer-capture APIs.
- Kept bounded drag-to-look and keyboard flight.
- Added a permanently visible Return to bridge action.
- Kept all initial and restored viewpoints centered on the bridge.

